
== cmdln operations performed to get my env up with my github dotfiles ==
* obtain an authorized github ssh key, then clone repo
>>>
git clone git@github.com:tdowg1/dotfiles
<<<

* append the following to .bashrc
>>>
if [[ -f ~/.mainly.sh ]] ; then
    . ~/.mainly.sh
fi
<<<

* manually source desired '.mainly.sh' script.
** do this so can get the $ZOMG_DOTFILES variable.
** NOTE: currently, this is what I'm doing
>>>
source dotfiles/home-machines/.mainly.sh
<<<

* create symlinks to main bash configs
>>>
ln -s $ZOMG_DOTFILES/.mainly.sh
ln -s $ZOMG_DOTFILES/.aliases.sh
ln -s $ZOMG_DOTFILES/.functions.sh
ln -s $ZOMG_DOTFILES/.variables.sh
<<<

* Open a new terminal and ensure env gets set up OK.
* deploy the rest of the other dotfiles
>>>
cdd
./dotfiles.sh install
<<<

